paragraphs:
[11]
The Delegate concluded as follows:
"Not only is Me Duchesne's file invoked by Henry Sztern closed, but
- considering the nature of the request led by Me Duchesne which consisted of a request for a portion of the federal sales tax refunds;
- considering that the case of Me Duchesne, Henry Sztern & Associés Inc. was acting in his capacity as trustee and that Henry Sztern and Henry Sztern & Associés Inc. were not personally involved;
- considering that the question of protecting client/prosecutor confidentiality is not relevant in the present case;
- considering that the report to be made to the Superintendent of Bankruptcies and its conclusions fall within the application of the disciplinary and ethical principles arising from the
Bankruptcy law
and not from the principles arising from the exercise of the rights of creditors in bankruptcy;
- considering that no attorney/client privilege exists between the undersigned and Henry Sztern and Henry Sztern & Associés Inc.;
- considering that the undersigned has no personal interest in the file relating to Me Duchesne; the alleged conflict of interest is ill-founded [sic] in law."
